message:
Have you gone to Kakariko? Impa gives you a few tips.

Basically theres 4 beasts, one per "race" (Zora, Goron, Gerudo, Rito). The most common 'first' one seems to be Zora since it's the closest to your starting area-ish.

Hope that was vague enough but still helpful lol
Flies? or Dragonflies
Assistant in Hateno lab. Sells em all I believe
I think it's ambient... I get distracted by them too... Or plain flowers in fields not meant to be picked lol

at work, so I can't check now but how far is rupee bowling from hebra tower? Also, I have the doublet and 1 or 2 1level cold resist food. Is getting there reasonable without burning through my stash? (and does the timer tick during the actual bowling game?
I see a bunch on the road to zoras... if I recall correctly

The scales are eventually used for gear but the first of each, you'd want for the 3 spring quests, really don't think it's worth cooking them

Also, don't worry about that piece yet... There's 2 other climbing pieces you can get to help in the meantime and they're way easier to get to
hmmm, you're making me wanna not clear zora and go to rito lol
does the weapon matter for flurry rushes?
can you pick em up?
Kakariko has one. Has the Hylian set and the stealth set
Lynel from Plybius mountain before the Divine Beast Ruto fight?

ok, I just need to have the flame weapon on my back right? since a torch is useless during the game I assume.

If so, where's a quick spot to grab a fire weapon lol only have a great frostblade, frostspear and thunder spear
touché. ok guess I gotta figure out how the eff to get to the ritos lol
Woo! Thanks, imma go bowling tonight! Assuming I don't get raped by the guardians surrounding the central tower lol, think I can see it from the tower to better plan my trek?
Ditto, I walked into the shrine for the third, took a pic and fucked right out lol
Found it! :)
